    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rooting for WordPerfect</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kevin Rothman letter on Joel Brinkley's Sept 21 article on word processing software notes Adobe Acrobat is application, not format</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The column about WordPerfect says that the opinions of Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson are published in three formats: Adobe Acrobat, HTML and WordPerfect. Adobe Acrobat is an application, not a format. The format it uses is P.D.F., which stands for Portable Document Format. To say a document is in Adobe Acrobat format is like saying a Web page was coded in Netscape (rather than HTML).</p>
        <p>KEVIN ROTHMAN  New York</p>
      </block>
